E077.description: With rising tension with the USSR forcing Japan ever cloaser to its allies in the western hemisphere, the have decided to make the greatest act of friendship they can and join our glorious nation!
E077.description1: We welcome them with open arms! However India is trying to claim South East Asia...
E077.description2: We are stretched thin as it is without the another area to defend.
E077.unique_event_name: Japan applies to join the AU!
E077.title: Japan applies to join the AU!

E076.description: As expected, the depression has caused a crash in stocks.
E076.title: Stock Market Crash!

E054.description: America is collapsing and we get to divy it up!
E054.title: America is divided!

E090.description: With the fall of the UBSR government, we have the opportunity to expand westwards.
E090.description2: Perhaps now is now is not the time for war with the west.
E090.title: The UBSR is in crisis!

E011.description: Basically to give the zombies a chance I've made them Op as fuck
E011.title: Balancing zombies

E053.description: America surrenders and we get to divy it up!
E053.title: America is divided!

E010.description: After centuries of uninhabiabil;ity, the chamical weapons dropped on Anatolia have given rise to new humanoid life! But it seems less than friendly...
E010.description1: What are we supposed to do?
E010.title: Something in Anatolia...

E089.description: It is time to reclaim the Statue of Liberty, and return it to France!
E089.title: Take back Liberty!

E078.description: With rising tension with the USSR to the west, and war potentially on the horison, it may be wise to get as close the the AU as we possibly can be: a member state.
E078.title: Should we join the AU?

E050.description: With a defeat such as this, we won't hold them for long...
E050.description1: We shall burn like the pheonix as we fall, and one day we shall be reborn.
E050.description2: Please, we beg of you, let us live!
E050.title: We've lost the capital!

E009.description: The Habsburg princes ruling your domains are demanding more autonomy as the situation deteriorates, what will you do? It seems tha the only option is to gran them autonomy! (May not work)
E009.description1: Forcably annex your vassals and place them under more direct control
E009.description2: Give them a bit more independence, how bad can it be?
E009.title: Crisis is brewing
E009.description3: Cross their palms with silver and hope for the best

E008.description: Terrorists are bombing our infrastructure, making it harder to construct buildings.
E008.description1: Send soldiers home from the frontlines to deal with it
E008.description2: We can't afford to send our soldiers home
E008.title: Terrorist Attacks
E008.answer2: Leave the police to deal with it
E008.description3: Nothing we can do for now, focus on the war

E049.description: The American Union's victory has empowered us as the new leaders of the United Blue Socialist Republics!
E049.title: America leads the UBSR!

E034.description: Printing all this money to pay the workers is putting a dent in the economy!
E034.title: Inflation
E034.description3: It'll be expensive but it's the best shot we have.

E007.description: Long after the war, the effects of Japanese chemical bombings still lingers to this day...
E007.title: Suffering from chemical weapons

E005.description: The UBSR government has been captured! Our glourious nation is in ruins!
E005.title: The Government Falls

E071.description: Our investment is paying off massively!
E071.title: Stock price skyrockets in UBSR!

E032.description: A holiday isn't enough to stave off the coming storm...
E032.description1: What can we do after all?
E032.title: It's getting worse

E015.description: The capital has fallen, what should we do????
E015.description1: If we're going down, they're coming with us. (Starts rebels in the USSR)
E015.title: Sarge, We're Sinking!

E047.description: Which nation do we install as the new leader of the UBSR?
E047.title: Who leads the UBSR?

E023.description: Forces from the ARF (Agartha Resistance Force)
E023.title: Assistance has arrived!

E031.description: Your attempts at calming the situatio  have done nothing. Civil war is upon us.
E031.title: Civil War
E031.description3: Surely there is a diplomatic solution?

E029.description: With the export of Chinese labour to foreign arkests, and Japanese refusal to make an official apology for the events of ww2 all those years ago, unrest is growing.
E029.description1: Announce a national holiday to celebrate our recovery, and to keep the population happy.
E029.title: Unrest

E107.description: We have captured important land in India. We could force them to surrender our claimed land.
E107.description1: Let us not let this war drag on, enough life has been lost already.
E107.description2: This is a victory of moral only if the enemy still breathes!
E107.title: Force a surrender?

E106.description: Thinking to feast on our territory whilst we are distracted, China has demanded we cede land to them.
E106.description1: War with China would be devastating. We cannot confront them so openly.
E106.description2: This is our land and ours alone. Nobody can take it from us by any means!
E106.title: China Demands Land
E106.answer2: We shall not stand for this!

E025.description: Agartha has been defeated, at last we may rest easy. But what do we do with our defeated enemy?
E025.description2: Take their technology ad use it for ourselves.
E025.title: It's over
E025.answer2: Let them live, at a cost
E025.description3: Every scraap of money in that hellhole is ours by right!
E025.answer3: Extort them for all they've got

E001.description: With the price of oil skyrocketing, our economy has begun to feel the flames of a crisis.
E001.description2: Make more use of the Arabian oil reserves
E001.title: Oil Crisis

E024.description: They have sent us a gift!
E024.title: Cordial relations with Agartha
E024.description3: We need no charity from these scum

E105.description: With India already in conflict, we may be able to threaten them into surrendering land.
E105.description1: If India refuses, it will mean a war that we cannot necessarily win.
E105.description2: Tibet is rightful Chinese territory, we must take it back!
E105.title: Press Claims

E026.description: We have recieved a shipment of supplies from beneath
E026.title: Supplies from beneath

E022.description: Agartha has risen from the depths! They have already defeated one of our number, but now we must unite against them!
E022.title: The Call For Aid

E088.description: Should we invest into the economy of the great powers?
E088.title: Should we invest?

E087.description: This is just so the great powers have nukes dw
E087.title: (Ignore this)

E028.description: Agartha is demanding that we cede land
E028.title: They are making demands

E104.description: The territories of Central America have been brought back under our control, god bless the United States!
E104.description1: Expand further, let nothing stand in our path!
E104.description2: Consolidate our gains and establish a stable frontier
E104.description3: Threaten war unless northern South America submits to our rule
E104.title: We Have Retaken Central America!

E044.description: The Oil Crisis has set off a huge catastrophe! With oil skyrocketing, the cost to operate machinery and automate production increases. The factories fail to produce enough goods, and thus shut down. This leads to mass unemployement, which has made the  the economic situation even worse, and so the cycle goes round and round, and at last it has found a breaking point.
E044.title: A Second Depression
E044.answer3: Use the oil we got from the UBSR

E042.description2: (Try and capture Arabia to progress the plot)
E042.title: They accepted!

E062.description: An attempt to unify the Iberian peninsula has recently failed to go through. It appears Iberia shall remain fractured for the forseeable future.
E062.title: Iberian Unification Plan Fails!

E012.description: With revolts taking place in far off lands, the homeland has begun to simmer with discontent.
E012.description1: Any discontent will not be tolerated. All must sing the government's praises.
E012.description2: Allow them independence, why not after all?
E012.unique_event_name: Do You Hear The People Sing?
E012.title: Do You Hear The People Sing?

E103.description: Our rapid printing of money has caused it to become worthless! Now our children play with stacks of cash instead of wooden blocks!
E103.description1: This would give them huge amounts of control over our economy however...
E103.description2: Our forces shall keep us from civil war!
E103.answer1: Let the USSR prop us up
E103.title: The currency collapses!

E021.description: Sir, our war hasn't gone as planned. They are using weapons the like of which we have never seen before! Our army is gone, what do we do?
E021.description1: There is no shame in asking for assistance under these circumstances.
E021.description2: Our mighty nation needs no aid.
E021.title: They are coming.

E051.description: America's capital has fallen, and now they beg for peace like the cowards they are!
E051.description1: We must crush this threat to all civilized peoples.
E051.description2: They have offered both money and land, why not? (lands will be given to subjects)
E051.title: America begs for peace!
E051.answer2: Accept and hand out their lands

E057.description: With a Wallace victory in the new election, the United States has transitioned to democratic socialism. Although some claim the "democratic" part is only short term...
E057.title: Wallace victory in election!

E084.description: America is damding we submit to their rul, or they will be forced to reclaim SEA by force!
E084.description1: We shall never bow to such lowly scum!
E084.description2: We cannot avoid subjication, but perhaps we can negotiate retaining some level of autonomy... (May be annexed, may not)
E084.title: America demands we submit!
E084.description3: What can we do against such an overwhelming foe?

E013.description: Riots in the streets. The populus is angry.
E013.unique_event_name: Singing The Song Of Angry Men
E013.title: Singing The Song Of Angry Men

E102.description: Our rapid printing of money has started to cause issues
E102.description1: It can't be that bad, right?
E102.description2: Adopt the currency of our neighbour: the UBSR
E102.description3: Adopt the currency of our neighbour: the USSR
E102.title: Inflation!

E006.description1: Officially apologise for the genocide of the Chinese population.
E006.description2: The chemical weapons dropped by the Japanese have dissapated!
E006.title: China Recovers!
E006.description3: Use cheap Chinese labour and export production to China

E030.description: Our army isn't able to hold them off nowthat they have armed themselves.
E030.description1: More soldiers, more guns, more fighting.
E030.description2: Oops! Didn't mean to do that, sorry!
E030.title: IT'S NOT WORKING!
E030.description3: I'm sorry to hear that you have taken it this way, but my massacre of innocent protestors was for their own good...

E020.description: We have truly found something amazing: a new civilization beneath the earth, named Agartha. How do we treat them?
E020.description1: Pathetic insects! They tunnel through our rot! We shall crush them like the ants they are!
E020.description2: Greetings, my new friend! I hope that together we may do great things in the world.
E020.title: Contact!
E020.description3: My most gracious king, you who are so greater than I, I am honoured by your presence.

E085.description: India has submitted to our authority!
E085.description1: Who can resist our might, after all?
E085.title: India accepts our terms!

E100.description: We can't keep up this spending. We have to slow down!
E100.description1: Let's slow down a little here...
E100.description2: We're the government right? Just make more money!
E100.title: Running low on cash

E099.description: The great powers have agreed to aid us, but as we suspected it will require us to submit so much autonomy we are essentially a vassal. All that remains now is to decide whowe shall become the puppet of.
E099.description1: They wish to have secure control of the Baltic, and are the strongest nation on Earth right now.
E099.description2: They would be delighted to have a foothold in Europe, and are strong enough tonprotect us if need be.
E099.title: We have our aid...
E099.description3: A safe bet. We have always had good relations with them, and they are close to home.

E096.description: The United States has cried out for aid against the communist expansion in Asia. How do we respond?
E096.description1: If the Soviets wish to expand, who are we to stop them?
E096.description2: We must not stand idly by as communism's tendrils spread across the globe ever further!
E096.title: America cries out!

E019.description: Faint radio signals have been detected, seemingly coming from deep beneath the earth. Should we investigate? (Warning: under construction)
E019.description2: We may want to let sleeping beasts lie... (Dismiss this questline forever)
E019.title: Our Scientists Found Something!

E067.description: Our investment is paying off massively!
E067.title: Stock price skyrockets in AU!

E004.description1: We have been oppressed for too long!
E004.title: Revolution Is Coming

E098.description: The old machinery of state and industry has finally kicked the bucket. Riots, food shortages, and inflation are all common.
E098.description1: We can look to a foreign power to aid us, but that will give them a lot of control over us...
E098.description2: Just pay off everything! Buy new machinery, hire new workers, pay formore food, it's fine!
E098.title: The economy is collapsing!

E083.description: The IPZ has launched a series of coups across South East Asia, stealing what is rightfull ours!
E083.description1: We can't afford a war right now.
E083.description2: They shall be allowed to live. At a price...
E083.title: Indian Coup!
E083.description3: They shall be crushed under our boots like insects.

E060.title: Referendum Results
E060.answer3: We'll have to wait to find out!

E018.description: We have been sluaghtering Buddhists and Muslims for a wile now, and it's starting to take a toll. What do we do?
E018.description2: It's not very good for our population. Or anything elsefor that matter
E018.title: The Purge

E081.description: After the recent union of the EAF and AU, India has at last dropped its claims on PTO and EAF territories in South East Asia.
E081.title: India drops claims on SEA!

E097.description: After decades without changr to our technology, foreign policy, or infrastructure, cracks are beginning to show.
E097.description1: Although unpopular, these reforms to our legal and economic structure must happen or we shall fall behind the other powers.
E097.description2: Our policies have been working for decades, surely thay shall not fail us now?
E097.title: Stagnation!

E063.description: The great powers of the world are clamouring for investment into their economies, who do we listen to?
E063.description1: The UBSR is mighty, socialist, and democratic! The best of both worlds! They are surely the best choice!
E063.description2: The USSR is the mightiest socialist nation on earth! They are surely the best choice!
E063.title: Opportunity for investment!
E063.description3: The American union is the mightiest democratic power on earth! They are surely the best choice.

E002.description: The Oil Crisis has set off a huge catastrophe! With oil skyrocketing, the cost to operate machinery and automate production increases. The factories fail to produce enough goods, and thus shut down. This leads to mass unemployement.
E002.title: The New Depression
E002.answer3: Use the oil we got from the UBSR

E059.description: A vote is to be cast! Will we unify?
E059.unique_event_name: A referendum is to be held!
E059.title: A referendum is to be held!

E017.description: The spies had spread further than we feared... THE MOTHERLAND IS REVOLTING!
E017.description1: We are in a state of emergency!
E017.title: The Motherland Is At War!

E016.description: Enemy spies have conspired against us! Europe is revolting! Oh yeah, there's a rebellion there too.
E016.title: Rvolution in Europe

E101.description: How do we cut back our spending? Which budgets do we slash?
E101.description1: Who needs and education system anyway?
E101.description2: We're not in any wars after all
E101.title: What budget do we cut?

E080.description: With the AU intergrating the EAF, there is great uproar in the government! A perfect time to sieze power has arisen, just between America taking over and th old government leaving. Should w launch a coup?
E080.title: A Golden Opportunity!

E086.description: India accepts, but wishes for a level of autonomy.
E086.title: India accepts!

E058.description: Request the UBSR government allows Iberia to unify
E058.description2: (If anyone selects this Iberia might be unified)
E058.title: Request To Unify

E056.description: With the global depression hampering our imports and exports, we can't buy food. As you can imagine, this makes our lack of agriculture an etremely prominent issue. Alongside this, oil is used in fertilisers making the deficit a great issue
E056.title: Agricultural  Issues

E003.description: As the world goes up in flames, the UBSR must make a difficult decision.
E003.description1: Send money and resources to those around us to help stave off the worst of the depression, and invite those worst affected to our nation to live among us.
E003.description2: Seal ourselves awayh to stave off the effects of the depression
E003.title: The World Burns
E003.description3: With our neighbours so weak, why shouldn't we squeeze them dry of money?

E095.description: The USSR is coming to dominate Asia. What shall we do about it?
E095.description1: Call the non communist powers of the world to combat communism.
E095.description2: Demand that they end their advances
E095.title: Communism Rises...

E014.description: Do you hear the people sing? Singing the song of angry men. IT IS A MUSIC OF A PEOPLE WHO WILL NOT BE SLAVES AGAIN!
E014.unique_event_name: A PEOPLE WHO WILL NOT BE SLAVES!
E014.title: A PEOPLE WHO WILL NOT BE SLAVES!

E041.description: Do we follow through with our threats?
E041.description2: (Try and capture Arabia to progress the plot)
E041.title: They refused.
E041.answer1: Back down, we can't afford a war
E041.answer2: Follow through, we need the oil

E055.description1: We shall be the mightiest nation in the world with all this steel!
E055.title: Our steelmaking is incredible!

civilization_111.name: United States of the Americas
civilization_111.group_name: United States of the Americas, Great power, ARF

civilization_109.name: South Georgia and the South Sandwiches Islands
